name: The Velvet Lounge
description:
Washington D.C. has been known as a national center for the arts and for amazing performing arts centers like the Kennedy Center and the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts.  The Velvet Lounge isn't like any of those places, but it does schedule excellent local performers specializing in psych, punk, and rock.  As anyone that has bought tickets to performances at the Velvet Lounge knows, the focus here is on excellent music, inexpensive drinks, and great people.  

The Velvet Lounge sets itself apart from the other bars and clubs on U Street by keeping it simple.  Bands play upstairs to frenzied crowds while those looking for relief from the crowds can linger downstairs, and there's nearly always someone interesting to talk to.  Drinks are simple and inexpensive; people looking for elaborate, $10 organic cocktails will be out of luck.  The schedule of performers will never feature a big name star, but will feature talented, popular musicians that are at the heart of the local music scene.  Audiences looking for a nitty, gritty live music experience should check out the frequent happenings at the Velvet Lounge.

Check the schedule above to see what performers (and maybe parties) the Velvet Lounge has lined up for this week, or just stop in to one of Washington D.C.'s most authentic live music venues.

name: Grog & Tankard
description:
202-333-3114

The Grog and Tankard has been a local favorite for 40 years.  
It’s the longest running bar with live music in the DC Metropolitan area, best
known for hosting a variety of local and nationally known music bands.  
Vertical Horizon, Hootie and the Blowfish, Lost Trailers, and thousands of
others have played at the Grog.  "If it's not happening for you at the Grog,
you need to reassess" - Matt Scannell, singer and guitarist for Vertical
Horizon.

The friendly atmosphere, great music, and stacked bar with 14 microbrews
on tap make the Grog and Tankard the perfect place for a break any night
of the week.  See you at the Grog!

name: Fadó Irish Pub
description:
Located in the downtown cultural quarter, we are next to all the action of the MCI center.

Next time you happen to be down here for a game or concert, stop by Fadó for a pint, dinner, brunch or just some good craic!

Our cozy locale is perfect for office lunches, family outings, and fun filled nights. For the latest updates of sports, music, and events, join our mailing list.

We are happy to bring you the best in live Irish sporting events, such as rugby, hurling, and Gaelic football. Speaking of Gaelic football, Fadó is proud to sponsor our local DC Gaels. Escape to another time and place when you step into Fadó.

name: DC9 Nightclub
description:
Washington D.C.'s U Street is home to numerous bars, clubs, and live music venues, but none more popular than DC9; and for good reason.  DC9 schedules some of the best local musicians and musical events in town, and provides a first class facility to host them.  Dozens and dozens of tickets are bought by loyal regulars for these indie and alternative performances, and the main reason patrons come back to DC9 again and again.

Another reason is the club itself which, while not the biggest club around, provides numerous seating options to comfortably accommodate the large crowds that can show up any day of the week.  Modern furniture and lighting fixtures add some flair to the otherwise simply decorated club whose main eye candy is the long, heavy bar.  There is another, smaller bar and booths upstairs, but most people gravitate to the slightly raised stage where scheduled musicians perform nearly every day of the week.  It's also where the DJ stands every Friday night for the Liberation Dance Party, a dance night featuring the newest hottest electronic, hip-hop, and rock dance music.

Audiences at DC9 get the exciting events and scheduled performers of a big club, mixed with the friendliness and comfortability of a neighborhood bar.

name: Rock and Roll Hotel
description:
The Rock and Roll Hotel is Washington DC's most famous live venue and "hotel".  While the rooms may be limited, the schedule is variegated and jam-packed with all your favorite local rock acts and national indie performers. The Rock and Roll Hotel is also a chic venue ideal for private parties, weddings, bachelor parties, etc.  Whether its a private party or an intimate rock show, the Rock and Roll Hotel is the perfect venue to party like a rockstar.  Don't miss an event on the Rock and Roll Hotel schedule.  Use Eventful as your source for the Rock and Roll Hotel concert calendar and to purchase tickets for all your favorite shows!

Situated on bustling H Street in Northeast Washington DC, the Rock and Roll Hotel was built on the foundation of combining rock with accommodations.  Although the accommodations are limited, to a few rooms or so, the ground floor offers a pulsating stage that reverberates throughout the entire venue.  The Rock and Roll hotel features two floors, the first known as "The Lobby Bara" features space for 400 patrons, a DJ booth, and a main stage.  The second floor hosts 'The Hotel Bara" which features three private suites of different decor.  Moreover, the  Rock and Roll Hotel features some of the best up-and-coming rock bands in Washington DC.  Don't miss a performance on the Rock and Roll Hotel concert schedule. Register with eventful and receive updates regarding all the events that this kitsch "hotel" offers.

name: 9:30 Club
description:
The 9:30 Club Washington opened in 1980, the venue getting its name from its then-current address - 930 F Street, NW, Washington, D.C. During these early days, the 9:30 Club Washington provided a platform for rock and alternative bands primarily, showcasing the likes of The Police, The Ramones, Mod Fun and The Bangles.

In order to accommodate the increasingly impressive musical lineup as well as the growing number of fans demanding tickets, the 9:30 Club Washington was forced to close and relocate, reopening in a bigger space in 1996. In the years following, the 9:30 Club schedule saw some of the music industry's biggest hitters take to the venue's stage. The Red Hot Chili Peppers, O.A.R, Smashing Pumpkins, Radiohead and Bob Dylan are just a few of those major acts featured on the 9:30 Club schedule post-1996.

For all the latest news and up-to-date event information, check out the 9:30 Club schedule.

name: Lincoln Theatre
description: Before there was the Harlem Renaissance, there was Washington DC's Lincoln Theatre. Central to the rise of African-American theatre in the United States, the Lincoln Theatre has been a cultural treasure since 1922. The Lincoln Theatre schedule is jam packed with a variety of events that highlight America's multicultural experience. From Carrie Fisher to Alicia Keys, the range and scope of performers and genres is unparalleled. Join the Lincoln Theatre as it celebrates 90 years of the performing arts. Use Eventful as your source for the Lincoln Theatre schedule and to receive regular updates regarding all of your favorite local events. Built in 1922, the Lincoln Theater was host to performances by a variety of artists including Ella Fitzgerald, Billie Holliday, Nat King Cole, and Louis Armstrong to name a few. During the 1940s, President Franklin D. Roosevelt hosted several of his birthday parties at the Lincoln Theater. The theater fell into disarray after the 1968 Washington, D.C. riots and eventually shut its doors. A revival effort took place in 1993 when the theatre was named to the National Register of Historic Places. It was restored and reopened in 1994 with a performance of Ain't Got Long to Stay Here, a play detailing Martin Luther King Jr.'s biography. The theatre can comfortably host 1,250 patrons for events ranging from the performing arts, stand-up comedy, and live musical events from contemporary artists. It has recently become a haven for the revival of jazz music and has featured performances by Quincy Jones and Chuck Brown. The Lincoln Theatre is truly committed to offering the best performers regardless of background or genre. Don't miss a performance by your favorite musician, performer, poet, or playwright! Register with Eventful to receive regular updates regarding the Lincoln Theatre schedule and to purchase tickets for all of your favorite events.

name: Blues Alley
description:
Founded in 1965, Blues Alley is the nation's oldest continuing jazz supper club, having showcased internationally renowned concert hall artists such as Dizzy Gillespie, Sarah Vaughan, Nancy Wilson, Grover Washington Jr., Ramsey Lewis, Charlie Byrd, Maynard Ferguson and Eva Cassidy in a small intimate setting.

Located in the heart of historic Georgetown in an 18th century red brick carriage house, Blues Alley offers its patrons a unique ambiance, reminiscent of the jazz clubs of the 1920's and 30's.

Open seven days a week, Blues Alley specializes in authentic Creole cuisine, steak and seafood dishes (Dinner served from 6:00 pm). Blues Alley has designed several discounted packages available to groups of twelve or more, and can accommodate up to one hundred and twenty five for dinner and show.

name: Bohemian Caverns
description:
Washington DC's Bohemian Caverns has been the capital's premier jazz nightclub since 1926.  The Bohemian Caverns schedule is jam packed with all of your favorite local and national jazz performers and features a full restaurant and bar.  The club went into a period of decline during the '70s but has subsequently been revived to its former glory.  Join the Bohemian Caverns as it celebrates over 80 years as Washington DC's beloved Jazz venue.  Register with Eventful to receive regular updates and to purchase tickets for all of your favorite local events. 

The Bohemian Caverns restaurant and Jazz Nightclub is located at 11th and U Streets in NW Washington DC.  It was founded in 1926 as a venue for variety shows and was frequented by such legends as Duke Ellington and Cab Calloway.  By the 1950s the name of the club was changed to Crystal Caverns eventually settling on Bohemian Caverns.  During the 1960s, The Bohemian Caverns was the premier jazz club and ushered in the era of jazz music for the city.  The club was able to book jazz superstars such as Miles Davis, Shirley Horn, John Coltrane, and Charles Mingus.  

By the turn of the decade, however, the club went into a state of disarray and it was closed.  Following revitalization efforts in NW Washington DC, the club was renovated and reopened to its former glory.   Now the venue is once again DC's premier jazz nightclub, featuring several performances each week by national acts.  The venue also features a full service restaurant/bar and is the perfect venue for jazz aficionados.  Don't miss a date on the Bohemian Caverns concert calendar.  Use Eventful as your source for the Bohemian Caverns schedule and never miss out when your favorite performers visit a venue near you.

name: Zeba
description:
Featuring four separate areas – a front patio, a main bar, a dancefloor, and an outdoor deck – Zeba is a perfect place for a happy hour or late-night dancing to the hottest DJs.

Our cocktails are crafted with fresh fruit and house-blended purees and juices. On tap we feature a wide selection of microbrews that will satisfy the most demanding connoisseur. The drinks are complemented by our food menu which is simple but has already gained recognition among the patrons. Chicken kabob is marinated in our special blend of spices and is the best in Columbia Heights. Our pizza is made from scratch using only the freshest ingredients with a wide variety of toppings.
